GITHUB BASICS

just typing 'git' will show all commands

CLONE : clones a repo
- navigate to folder you want repo created in
- from your repo on github > repo > Code > Clone > Copy address
- git clone https://github.com/cwhiterite/cwhiterite.github.io.git
- Open folder in Visual Studio Code

STATUS : gets status of local branch
- git status

ADD : adds file or all files to be commited
- git add test.txt   
- git add . 
- git add -A

RESTORE : discard changes
- git restore test.txt

COMMIT : commit with message, ready to push
- git commit -m "Hello World!"
- if forgot -m, Esc :wq will return to cmd

PUSH : pushes commits to github.com repo 
- git push

PULL : pulls files down from github.com
- git pull